	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Fri Mar 16, 2007 10:47 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Norrin_Radd wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Ok, so I've started making music with FamiTracker, so I actually need to know how to make DPCM samples now, not just make wavs that sound like them. Tepples, I am really exited to use your program for this, but I really have no idea how to convert the files.</div>
<br />From the command prompt, do this:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">81 bass.wav bass.dmc</div>
<br />The sample rate of bass.wav should be 4182, 4710, 5264, 5593, 6258, 7046, 7919, 8363, 9420, 11186, 12604, 13982, 16885, 21307, 24858, or 33144 Hz.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


